{"id":14881079,"mediaExerciseId":"bc7a070a-f697-4d8b-a7bc-6118fe9c22fb","exerciseName":"30","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612313,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":236,"solutions":[{"id":6020266,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, **we have a data-only about the coupon rate, and we should find the maturity.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"We should focus on the part that the bond is selling at the par value. This information gives us two conclusions: the face value is equal to the present value, and the yield to maturity is the same as the coupon rate.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"In the exercise where the face value is missing, we assume it is \\$1,000 or \\$10,000.\n\nLet's assume the face value is \\$1,000 and write down the formula and insert all the data.\n\n$$\\text{Price}=\\text{C}\\times\\dfrac{1-\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)^\\text{-n}}{\\text{YTM}}+\\dfrac{\\text{P}}{\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)^\\text{n}}$$\n\nC-coupon of the bond \n\nYTM-yield to maturity\n\nP-par value\n\nn-time","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The only thing that we need to calculate now is coupon value.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{coupon value}&=\\text{coupon rate}\\times\\text{face value}\\\\[15pt]\n&=10\\%\\times\\$1,000\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\$100\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe coupon value is \\$100.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"If we insert all the data in the formula, it will look like 